Description: Lightweight clipboard history manager
 Clipman monitors your clipboard and stores a history of text and images.
 It ignores file/folder copies and multi-image copies.
 Press Super+V (configurable) to open the floating history window.
 .
 Features:
  - Stores up to 50 clipboard entries (text + single images)
  - Searchable history
  - Configurable global hotkey
  - Auto-starts with desktop session
  - Compact C/GTK3 binary
